This is the notes for the 1.js

.constructors 
    .method that runs automatically when I create a new object from a class 
    .its how I set up the object's initial state - its properties, defaults, and any logic needed at creation time 
    >it receives the initial values I pass in 
    .assigns the values to the (this) object
    .runs any set up logic (validation, defaults, computed values)
    .guarantees every object starts in a valid state 
    .its always named constructor 

>> 
    .{} - new creates the empty object 
    .(this) points to that new object === attaching properties to the new object 
    .constructor always returns the object automatically; never use return in a constructor 

Importance:
.enforce the required data 
.prevent invalid objects 
.set defaults 
.prepare internal state 
.make objects predictable and safe to use  

